verses.roman:
nā jāni,--ki khāñā matta hañā nāce, gāya
hāse, kānde, paḍe, uṭhe, gaḍāgaḍi yāya

synonyms: nā jāni—we do not know; ki—what; khāñā—eating; matta—mad; hañā—becoming; nāce—He dances; gāya—chants; hāse—laughs; kānde—cries; paḍe—falls down; uṭhe—gets up; gaḍāgaḍi yāya—goes rolling on the ground.
translation: " 'We do not know what He eats that makes Him become mad, dancing, singing, sometimes laughing, crying, falling down, jumping up and rolling on the ground.
